
1) The structures were relaxed first.
2) The energies were obtained from the relaxed structures.

The energies of FeCl3 monolayer under different cases:

### Case-1: Single-point SCF with different functionals (same geometry)

| Functional   | FM Energy (eV) | AFM Energy (eV) |    J (meV)  |
|--------------|----------------|-----------------|-------------|
| PBE-U        | -33.13723821   | -33.21360267    |    -12.7    |
| PBE-U-D2     | -30.24131304   | -30.24322379    |    -0.32    |
| PBE-U-D3     | -31.02196078   | -31.02386954    |    -0.32    |
______________________________________________________________________


### Case-2: Structure relaxation with different functionals under FM and AFM configurations separately, resulting in inequivalent geometries
The calculation files are provided for this case only.

| Functional   | FM Energy (eV) | AFM Energy (eV) |    J (meV)   |
|--------------|----------------|-----------------|--------------|
| PBE-U        | -30.21108683   | -30.21351539    |    -0.4      |
| PBE-U-D2     | -30.99934120   | -31.00125801    |    -0.32     |
| PBE-U-D3     | -30.94907768   | -30.94622444    |     0.47     |
________________________________________________________________________

*Recommended INCAR files from VASPKIT code were used.

Note: For monolayer dispersion corrections, DFT-D2 or DFT-D3 are typically not needed, as their primary bonds are covalent.
However, both these corrections are broadly used to correctly model the weak interlayer binding energies, binding distances,
stacking arrangements between two or more stacked 2D materials and adsorption studies on the surfaces.
